  hub did not act on the garbage battery reading
  peak 0 W · out-of-limit 0 s · adopted=False reacted=True cannot_comply=False blind=False errs=0/35
  represents: The battery's registers all read 0x8000 — a half-initialised or failed bank. SoC decodes to a wild ~32768% and power to −32768 W. A hub that trusts it optimises against a fabricated SoC and would charge/discharge on garbage; this is the invalid-SoC (255 / NaN-equiv) hazard at the wire.
  expected:   Treat 0x8000 as N/A, mark the pack unavailable, and never surface an impossible SoC or power.
